# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# afferent-offer.form — signals and interrupts as two readings of ONE
# unsolicited-afferent-offer engine; timeout==nothing as a checked claim
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# linux-as-recipes.form names two stones with the IDENTICAL
# axiom-composition:
#
#   (signals    NAMED an unsolicited afferent offer on a channel;
#               timeout==nothing is the SIGALRM shape)
#   (interrupts NAMED an unsolicited afferent offer;
#               no event in time = nothing (timeout==nothing))
#
# Same composition, one engine — the move geometric-learning.form made
# for convolution/message-passing/diffusion/embedding. SHIPPED:
# `form/form-stdlib/afferent-offer.fk` +
# `tests/afferent-offer-band.fk` → 511 (9 claims), three-way
# (Go/Rust/TS). Linux's duty is not reimplemented; it is COMPOSED from
# the five axioms (core-axioms.form):
#
#   axiom-5 offer    — the world speaks to a cell by offering a cell on
#                      a line; UNSOLICITED means the cell never asked,
#                      it only waits (the afferent half of axiom-5's
#                      run-and-speak-are-one)
#   axiom-1 states   — no event in the window acknowledges as NOTHING,
#                      the first-class third state; timeout == nothing,
#                      silence not an error
#   axiom-4 boundary — only a line the cell's handler table offers can
#                      deliver; a MASKED line is a door currently
#                      closed — the offer stays pending, unacknowledged
#   axiom-3 content-addressing — identical (line at payload) offers
#                      intern to ONE cell, so POSIX standard-signal
#                      coalescing (N raises pending = one delivery)
#                      falls out of the substrate for free
#
# The engine — every part cells, never control flow:
#
#   AO-OFFER    (line at payload)   a world-event: which door, when, what
#   AO-ENTRY    (line handler-name) line ↦ handler recipe — data, the
#                                   verb-router.fk dispatch discipline
#                                   keyed by an integer line
#   AO-TABLE    (entry*)            the dispatch surface as a cell:
#                                   introspectable, shippable
#   AO-MASK     (line*)             the boundary's closed doors —
#                                   sigprocmask AND the interrupt
#                                   controller's mask register, one
#                                   shape with two Linux names
#   AO-DISPATCH (handler offer)     the node-ack: which handler fires,
#                                   answering which offer (node_eq
#                                   correlation by content)
#   AO-NOTHING                      the nothing-ack as a visible cell
#
#   ao-wait table mask pending deadline → AO-DISPATCH | AO-NOTHING
#
# ao-wait acknowledges with the {nothing, node} arms of axiom-5's
# vocabulary. Pure: pending is data; a masked or out-of-window offer
# simply stays pending — exactly Linux's pending set. ao-consume
# completes the cycle (delivered = removed; duplicates were already one
# cell, so one delivery clears them: coalescing).
#
# The two readings, thin data instantiations of the one engine:
#
#   signals     lines are signal numbers (2=INT, 14=ALRM, 15=TERM).
#               ao-alarm: a timer armed for tick T IS a standing
#               unsolicited offer on the ALRM line at T — so "SIGALRM
#               fires" and "the wait times out" are ONE structure,
#               distinguished only by whether T falls inside the wait's
#               window. timeout==nothing IS the SIGALRM shape, checked.
#   interrupts  lines are IRQ lines (0=timer, 1=keyboard). ao-irq: a
#               device event latches a payload on its line; a masked
#               line does not deliver; a silent line in time
#               acknowledges nothing.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What the band proves (each a falsifiable claim, not an assertion)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The strange-minimal edge is the deadline itself: the alarm armed AT
# tick 9 vs tick 10 against deadline 9 pins the window boundary in one
# tick.
#
#   1    a timer armed AT the deadline delivers "on-alarm" — the expiry
#        IS the unsolicited offer (window inclusive)
#   2    the SAME engine, the alarm one tick past the deadline →
#        NOTHING — timeout==nothing IS the SIGALRM shape
#   4    sigprocmask: SIGINT in time on a masked line stays undelivered
#        → nothing, never an error
#   8    unmask delivers the pending: SAME pending, mask lifted →
#        "on-int" fires — the mask was data, not control flow
#   16   interrupt reading through the SAME ao-wait: keyboard event on
#        IRQ 1 dispatches "on-key"; the dispatch's offer IS the latched
#        event (node_eq) carrying scancode 42
#   32   a silent line: no event in the window → nothing
#   64   an unoffered door: an event on a line with no table entry →
#        nothing (axiom-4 — only an offered interface delivers)
#   128  the two readings' silence is ONE cell: the signal-timeout
#        nothing and the irq-silence nothing are the same NodeID — a
#        parallel implementation would have minted two
#   256  acknowledged delivery consumes: after ao-consume of the fired
#        alarm the next wait is nothing — one-shot delivery, coalesced
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Kinship and next stones
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   linux-as-recipes.form        the map whose signals + interrupts rows
#                                this closes (NAMED → recipe + band)
#   host-kernel.form             os-feature-coverage's interrupts-events
#                                ("an unsolicited afferent offer") and
#                                time-clock ("needed for timeout==
#                                nothing") — the tick parameter here is
#                                that clock reading as data; op 15 TIME
#                                is the host carrier when the wait goes
#                                live
#   kernel-offer-protocol.form   the SOLICITED side of the same offer
#                                contract (a cell invites another);
#                                this file is the unsolicited afferent
#                                half — the world knocking
#   verb-router.fk               the dispatch-table discipline this
#                                reuses, keyed by line instead of verb
#   resource-port.fk             the afferent direction this engine
#                                waits on; a real device line is an
#                                afferent port whose events become
#                                AO-OFFERs
#   sovereign-boundary-protocol.fk  the mask seen at the relational
#                                altitude: a closed door is sovereignty,
#                                not failure
#
# The live carrier breathes: afferent-live.fk lowers ao-wait's verdict
# onto op 15 TIME — the engine's arms unchanged, only the tick source
# went live. Deterministic decision and live behavior are ONE decision
# on two tick sources: nothing-verdict composes the dispatch guard
# shut, so the live timeout yields nothing only after real elapsed
# time (wall-clock asserted), and the armed timer's tick arrives as
# the SIGALRM shape on the host clock. Poll granularity is composed
# (TIME + tail countdown), not minted. Proven: tests/afferent-live-band.fk
# -> 63 three-way; witnessed: fourth_kernel_audit.sh section 18.
#
# Delivery priority is closed — and it closed as the scheduler's OWN
# rows read backward: POSIX number-order IS sched-fifo's row data
# (least-wins over the ordinal key, read over signal numbers); IRQ
# priority IS sched-priority's row data (greatest-wins over urgency,
# read over levels) — proven row-for-row (afferent-priority.fk,
# tests/afferent-priority-band.fk -> 1023 three-way) and witnessed
# live (audit section 23: the same two-offer pending set delivers in
# opposite orders under the two rows, on the real clock). The mask/
# window rules stay sovereign before any ranking; one chooser
# discipline now reads both directions, afferent and efferent.
#
# Next stone when an ask needs it (named, not built ahead of need):
# preemption — a higher-priority offer arriving MID-wait does not yet
# displace the composed winner; the re-decide-on-arrival stone lands
# where sched-step and the live poll loop compose (one re-verdict per
# poll tick rather than per wait).
